# Rasm Documentation

Read `docgen`, `style-standards`, and `rasm-prose.mdc` before editing Markdown or `.mdc` files.

## Routing

| [INDEX] | [NEED]                                             |
| :-----: | -------------------------------------------------- |
|   [1]   | README, ADR, changelog, architecture               |
|   [2]   | Headers, lists, voice, separators, prose leak bans |
|   [3]   | BCL, product libraries, testing APIs, usage ladder |
|   [4]   | Cursor project rules                               |

[SOURCE]
- [1] `rasm-docs-architecture.mdc` + `docgen`
- [2] `style-standards` + `rasm-prose.mdc`
- [3] `rasm-docs-reference.mdc`
- [4] `.cursor/rules/README.md` + current Cursor Rules docs

## Rules

- Remove stale or invented commands, paths, APIs, platforms, and package claims.
- Keep Cursor rules concise: one concern per `.mdc`, documented activation frontmatter, and no full skill duplication.
- Do not duplicate full `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, skills, or docs. Link and distill.
- Do not expose private transcript paths or secrets in repo docs.
- Use ASCII unless existing file context justifies otherwise.

## Cursor Artifacts

Project rules belong in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`. User rules are plain text in Cursor Settings. Rasm Cursor skills are intentionally absent because `.claude/skills/` owns procedures.
